photo.title: Aerial view of Four Embarcadero Center and the Embarcadero, San Francisco, California

description._content: Aerial photograph of Four Embarcadero Center (building in center of image) and the Embarcadero, San Francisco, San Francisco County, California. Included in this view to the north are: Financial District, Piers, Four Embarcadero Center (to the left), One Market Street (at about 5 o'clock), Hyatt Regency San Francisco (at about 6:30 o'clock), and San Francisco Bay.

photo.title: 70's Architecture

description._content: International Style Unite! I shot this from my hotel room at the Hyatt Regency. This view has not changed in 35 years. San Francisco is well known for it's collection of International Style, boxy and sterile askyscrapers. Embarcadero Center and the Transamerica pyramid are results of this style. Don't get me wrong, I love the pyramid, but it is stale and uniform. At least some of the latest skyscrapers offer more detail and variety.
